OL,3,CLeading WASPI campaigner's 10 year
OL,4,Cfight with government for compensation
OL,6,FWomen's unpaid labour "saved the state
OL,7,Fa fortune" the WASPI campaign chair
OL,8,Fhas claimed, as she called on the
OL,9,Fgovernment not to go back on their
OL,10,Fpromises.
OL,12,FRetired IT worker Angela Madden has
OL,13,Fspoken in depth about her 10-year
OL,14,Fdrive for compensation for female
OL,15,Fpensioners born in the 1950s who lost
OL,16,Fout financially from the state pension
OL,17,Fage being moved.
OL,19,FAngela, from Chesterfield, Derbyshire,
OL,20,Fstopped work in 2008 to care for her
OL,21,Felderly mother, and later her uncle.
