OL,3,CLeading WASPI campaigner's 10 year
OL,4,Cfight with government for compensation
OL,6,FBut the loss in what would have been
OL,7,Faccrued pension contributions -
OL,8,Fcombined with the pushing back of her
OL,9,Fstate pension age - have left her and
OL,10,Fmany others at a financial
OL,11,Fdisadvantage, something she describes
OL,12,Fas "an absolute injustice".
OL,14,FIt comes as the Secretary of State
OL,15,Flast week said the government would
OL,16,F"reconsider" its previous U-turn on
OL,17,Fpromises to compensate WASPI (Women
OL,18,FAgainst State Pension Inequality)
OL,19,Fcampaigners, made before the 2024
OL,20,Fgeneral election.
